				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So, since XNA is calling Present(), that's the one to use for vblank waiting then.<br />Then I started doing web searches about present().  I was reading a blog post on virtualdub.org, where the author talks about input events (keyboard and mouse) being horribly delayed by 5 seconds.  XNA only calls Present() in an Application.Idle event handler, so this is after the windows message queue is empty, and it avoids that problem.</div>

					
